<h2><a class="" name="common"></a>Common Methods</h2>

<h3>AWS</h3>
<ul>
    <li> On EC2 instancesm treat them like any other box with the options below.
    <li>RDS MySQL and RDS Aurora have automatic backups. Restoration is easy. 
</ul>

<h3>Backups</h3>
This is for your own servers. 
<ul>
  <li> It is recommened to make backups from a slave. You should routinely tun Percona Checksum
    on Masters and Slaves to make sure they are in sync. When backings up from a slave you want to record the Master binlog position and the Slave binlog position.:
    <ul>
      <li>mysqldump: 
    </ul>
</ul>
